               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>Dār al-Kutub, MS 4751 tibb is a modern copy (<date calendar="#Gregorian" notAfter="1942" notBefore="1942">1942</date>) of Damascus, Maktabat al-Asad 3152. This codex consists of two parts.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_4751_tibb-item1" n="1">
                     <locus from="1" to="164">pp. 1-164</locus>
                     <author key="person_81975562">
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/81975562" type="aut">ʿAbd al-Laṭīf al-Baǧdādī‏عبد اللطيف البغدادي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7765">كتاب تقدمة المعرفة لبقراط وتفسيره للشيخ الإمام الفاضل أبي الفضل عبد اللطيف بن يوسف بن محمد البغدادي</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7765">Hippocrates' Prognostics and Abd Latif Baghdadi's Commentary on it.</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7765">Kitāb Taqdimat al-Maʿrifa wa tafsīruh li l-šayḫ al-ʾimām al-fāḍil ʿAbi l-Faḍl ʿAbd al-Laṭīf ... al-Baǧdādī</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Egyptian National Library.</note>
                     <note>This is a copy of Hippocrates' Prognostics and ʿAbd al-Laṭīf al-Baǧdādī's Commentary on it.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_4751_tibb-item2" n="2">
                     <locus from="1" to="168">pp. 1-168</locus>
                     <author key="person_4405945">
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" type="aut">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7754">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7754">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7754">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction begins on <locus>p. 2</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: p. 4; Bk2: p. 34; Bk3: p. 84; Bk4: p. 119 (in p. 145, line 14, iv. 14 ends). Afterwards, the copy is missing several pages: p. 145, line 14: middle of i.4-16 p. 154: vii. 44 p. 155: vi. 35 p. 159: vii. 50-end. It is a copy of Ibn ʾAbī Ṣādiq's commentary although on the front page, this copy is entitled "The second part of Hippocrates' Prognostics and ʿAbd al-Laṭīf al-Baǧdādī's Commentary on it".</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
